					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">JunoMan wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">in the NMI you probably need to push the status registers as the inc will change the flags</div>
<br />Not necessary. On interrupts the flags are automatically pushed, and RTI restores them. You only need to push/restore A, X and Y, if you use them.</div>

